While now the fated Pequod had been so long afloat this voyage, the log and 
line had but very seldom been in use. Owing to a confident reliance upon other 
means of determining the vessel’s place, some merchantmen, and many whalemen, 
especially when cruising, wholly neglect to heave the log; though at the same 
time, and frequently more for form’s sake than anything else, regularly 
